A.3 Sample Code Transformation
To provide a concrete example of the system’s output, this section shows the transformation of a
standard sequential matrix multiplication function into a parallel version using OpenMP, as generated
by theqwen2.5model with the Tree of Thoughts strategy.
Original Sequential Code
void matmul(float* A, float* B, float* C, int n) {
for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
for (int j = 0; j < n; j++) {
C[i*n + j] = 0.0f;
for (int k = 0; k < n; k++) {
C[i*n + j] += A[i*n + k] * B[k*n + j];
}
}
}
}
